President Obama has declared a major disaster in South Dakota due to severe storms and flooding that occurred in September 2010. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state, local, and tribal recovery efforts. Funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Mark A. Neveau has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.